Subject: [PATCH 3/5] feat(consolidate): F.4 extract renderers + system-prompt
 helper to neutral modules
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Stage F.4 of the agent-loop consolidation (PR #185 landed Stage F.2/F.3
production cutover). All production callers now import renderer types
from their canonical home; the agent_loop.py shim is reduced to ~210
loc that only test fixtures still need.

## What moved where

**New module `src/tool_system/renderers.py` (257 loc)** — canonical
home for the symbols that have nothing to do with the agent loop's
flow:
  * `ToolEvent`, `AgentLoopResult` (dataclasses)
  * `ToolEventHandler`, `TextChunkHandler` (callable type aliases)
  * `summarize_tool_use`, `summarize_tool_result` (renderers — bodies
    verbatim from agent_loop.py, including the askuserquestion /
    sendusermessage / agent / task / toolsearch branches)
  * `_safe_call_handler`, `_emit_text_chunks` (handler utilities)

The neutral `tool_system` location (vs `tui/`) avoids the
`src/tui/__init__.py` → app → agent_bridge → agent_loop_compat
circular that the original ch05/F.4 design flagged.

**`src/query/agent_loop_compat.py` (+40 loc)** — gains
`build_effective_system_prompt(style_prompt, tool_context)`. Only
callers are the F.2/F.3 cutover code (headless + agent_bridge); lives
next to the adapter they use rather than in the deprecated agent_loop
module.

**`src/tool_system/agent_loop.py` (537 → 210 loc, -210)** — slimmed
to: deprecation header, `_call_provider_for_turn` (used by
`tests/test_agent_loop_image_size_propagation.py`), and
`run_agent_loop` (used by tests that haven't been ported yet). Renderer
symbols are re-exported from `renderers` for one deprecation cycle so
existing test imports keep working.

## Production importers migrated

7 src/ files now import from the canonical paths:
  * `src/entrypoints/headless.py` — renderers + build_effective_system_prompt
  * `src/tui/agent_bridge.py` — same
  * `src/tui/widgets/transcript_view.py` — summarize_tool_result
  * `src/tui/widgets/messages/assistant_tool_use.py` — summarize_tool_use
  * `src/repl/core.py` — ToolEvent + summarizers (dropped unused
    run_agent_loop import)
  * `src/tool_system/tools/agent.py` — summarize_tool_use
  * `src/query/agent_loop_compat.py` — renderer types from canonical

Zero src/ files now import from `src.tool_system.agent_loop` directly.

## Test fixture updates

Two patches needed updating because the underlying imports moved:
  * `tests/test_dangerous_skip_permissions.py` — was patching
    `headless_mod.run_agent_loop` which is no longer imported on
    headless. Updated to patch `run_query_as_agent_loop` (async)
    matching the same fix in `test_headless_cli.py` from PR #185.
  * `tests/test_repl.py::test_chat_uses_true_api_stream_for_simple_prompt`
    — patched `src.repl.core.run_agent_loop` to assert
    `assert_not_called()`. REPL no longer imports it (uses
    QueryEngine instead), so the assertion is structurally
    guaranteed. Removed the patch + assertion; chat_stream check
    remains as the primary signal.

